# A person who will [[exchange]] [[currency]] of one type for another for a fee or percentage.
#: {{ux|en|The '''money changer''' gave me rupees for my dollars.}}
#* '''1611''', Bible, King James version, Matthew 21:12,
#*: And Jesus went into the temple of God, and cast out all them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the '''moneychangers''', and the seats of them that sold doves, …
# A [[portable]] device for [[dispense|dispensing]] [[change]].
#* '''1969''', {{w|Maya Angelou}}, ''{{w|I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings}}'', New York: Bantam, 1971, Chapter 34, p. 224,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/iknowwhycagedbi000maya]</sup>
